recommended
arma 3 is a great game but it is not for everyone  beautiful visuals that stay in the realm of the realistic alot of games that have been released lately are quite beautiful but many of the visuals in these games are overdone and embellished arma manages to retain its beauty while never really going over the edge into unrealistic gameplay depth if youve always wanted to experience real lifelike military combat then arma is for you combat in this game is slow tactile and unforgiving if you go into combat with a call of duty rambo one man army mentality you will die it is complex to the point of near ridiculousness with the game using nearly every key on the keyboard for keybinds real physics wind mapping realistic scope alignment and several other things that bring the game as close to real combat as most people would ever want to be  map size if you have never played an arma game before then youre in for something special this game boasts the biggest map of any game i think ive ever played coming in just shy of being twice the size of washington dc  steam workshop the game has full workshop support with everything from new character models to new missions i havent seen many guns or vehicles but im sure theyll come with time  accessibility as i said at the beginning of this review this game is by no means for everyone the amount of content is staggering for a new player and getting used to the controls can be a nightmare if youre not dedicated to the process  limited community as with every game there are good people and bad people in the community you will find several people that are willing to help you learn the game and you will find alot of people willing to have patience with you but with that being said arma has a really dedicated and hardcore fanbasecommunity you will get on servers where no one is going to help you you will get on servers where no one is going to pay any attention to you and you will get on servers where you are going to be yelled atshot at for not doing your part there are communities in this game that use real military tactics have a full chain of command and have real military training  performance this game is not easy to run i play on an intel i7 45ghz and an evga gtx670 4gb model and i have trouble maxing the game out in single player in multiplayer youll find yourself turning nearly everything to low just to squeeze every bit of performance out of your system that you can if you are not running top of the line tech i do not suggest playing this game you may end up disappointed  you make your own fun if you are not familiar with arma then you need to read up a little before your purchase this game does not have a full campaign yet and offers very little gameplay outside of multiplayer while the game does have and extensive scenario creator if you are not familiar with how to use this feature the game is going to seem completely barren in terms of gameplay it is very much so a bare bones package if you dont understand how to make scenarios however if you teach yourself how to do this the possibilities are virtually limitless  quite offputting to new players i remember my first few days of playing arma ii and i remember fairly vividly how much i hated them trying to take the game in is alot for a person who has been used to playing typical games all their life if you put alot of time into the game youll find enjoyment but its a bit of a rocky road at first overall arma iii is a great game that i personally love but i cant speak for everyone some will love this game and some will absolutely hate it it is a great game if you can manage to get past the steep learning curve when considering purchasing this game keep in mind that alot of people that give it bad reviews probably dont play games like this very often this is not battlefield and nor is it call of duty and thats okay it is its own genre and deserves to be treated as such 7910
recommended
shooting is as fun and precise as ever and alongside the abundance of gigantic explosions vehicle missions and intense firefights it feels like the closest thing most of us will ever get to starring in an action film in that sense arma iii is the classic call of duty formula at its best with an important defining difference the emphasis on drone warfare the exoticbutgrounded weaponry and the attention to detail in the believably hightech signage and architecture makes arma iii feel strikingly plausible even when it strays into nonhistorical settings a number of other smaller design tweaks highlight the clever design of class creation in arma iii for instance perks now only affect your character leaving it to the attachments system to affect your weapon thus if you want to do something like fast reload which will make longtime players look for the sleight of hand perk youll need to hook up your weapon with a fast clip attachment the kill streak system has also been wisely replaced by score streaks making every match less about how many kills and in what consecutive order you get them in and more about doing whatever nets you the highest score this accomplishes a majorly important feat it makes every game less about your kill  death ratio sure it still wont keep people from obsessing over it but if you want to get it higher youre going to need to help with objectives arma iiis zombies mode is the deepest the franchise has seen even if its campaign narrative is reliant on the selfimposed stories arising from your roaming zombieslaughtering adventures with pals the team at bi could have played it safe and arma iii would have sold well but instead they challenged assumptions and pushed the series forward in awesome new directions itll be hard to return to a campaign where i dont have the ability to shape it and i simply cant imagine going back to the old loadout system now that pick 10 exists combined with the host of subtle and overt improvements to the array of other systems the additions to make it more appealing to esports and the more fleshed out zombies mode this is not just a fantastic call of duty game but one of the best shooters of the last decade 93 amasing
