this is a 1st3rd person war simulation engine not quite a game on its own yet arma iii comes with very little content on its own and it is ripe with missing features and bugs but the guys over at bohemia interactive have been dilligent with patches features and support theres an entire website dedicated to live bug tracking and suggestions with feedback from the developers which is incredibly rare that being said many users still continually suffer from lag and crashes and the game has very high requirements to run and look nicely despite the missing bugs and features the game has all the core components of a strong simulation game the developers have done well on bullet physics and the graphics look really nice on max on the other hand the game is very complex and the controls will be difficult to pick up for new players your bullets are not lazers that hit your target immediately you will need to range your target adjust the sight on your gun to the appropriate distance and lead them appropriately to have a chance of hitting them unless youre under 300m away then let your inner call of duty player out the games built in content consists of scenarios and the recently added campaign the scenarios and tutorials are introductions into the various attributes of the game from flying helicopters to assault diving to artillerty strikes the campaign feels like a bunch of scenarios strung together and adds very little to the game all things considered the campaign is bad and you wont want to play or remember it for long but you dont buy this game for the single player the multiplayer game modes are what put this game head and shoulders above other similar multiplayer games players can join a wide variety of different game modes that are downloaded and installed automatically for the player before joining the server there are only two maps a large map that bogs down servers with its sheer size and a smaller map that doesnt bog down the servers as much just like in arma 2 there are many guides tools and tutorials provided and created by the community in order to produce new and diverse game modes and content the popular dayz mod will likely not exist in arma 3 because of the upcoming standalone installment but the wasteland mode offers the same scavengingsurvival mechanics sans zombies there are also deathmatches missions and rpg modes to cater to every type of player the call of duty crowd would probably get bored by the slow pace of the game the battlefield 4 crowd will have much more common ground but might dislike the lack of polish in the game the arma 2 crowd will enjoy the game my tips for starting to play in any game mode in any lobby in any situation where youre unsure in any situation where you have no clue whats going on ask questions the community is incredibly responsive and helpful they will know the game better than you and their help will mean the difference between all your shots going right over the enemys head or right into the enemys head adjust your scopes range with pgup and pgdown you should probably stay out of global voice chat use  and  to change your chat channel stick to the blue team channel if youre not sure where you should be talking
