terribly optimized graphics engine but still very fun to play high frame rates arent too necessary in this game because your typical encounter is a much more realistic than bf4 distance which is usually 300m or more since bullets actually kill fast like in real life when hits are scored close quarters encounters are short and deadly clearing a building is actually dangerous unlike bf or cod and usually theres no lateral tracking to be done since people move slow compared to the absurdly unrealistic bf or cod games so 24 fps actually is quite playable in arma 3 i can play gta v on near ultra settings on 1080p at 110 fps to give you an idea of how poorly arma 3s graphics are optimized as for gameplay the game has a great story mode and awesome multiplayer dogfights in jets arent the stupid 60 mph dogfights like in bf4 but rather youre doing 300400 mph while trying to stay on his tail ive actually damaged my plane and pilot taking a nearly 9g turn to dodge 4 incoming missiles after i ran out of flares yes aircraft have realistic quantities of ammo and fuel as they should if you plan to fly anything you must have a mic and most servers require teamspeak which is lame since the game already has global side command group and vehicle channels along with direct communications proxy voice there is no need for ts unless if youre a braindead  who doesnt know how to utilize the ingame channels however you will find yourself short of servers to play on if you dont respect the admins most of whom play nothing but arma 3 and have a god complex stroke their fragile egos and all will be well for you weapons arent balanced which is nice because they arent balanced in real life in real life weapons are designed to be the best at the role they were meant for and thats how the weapons in arma 3 are coded the only balancing is the weight penalties ammo for a 50 cal or 127mm amr is freaking heavy in real life and so it is in arma 3 if you want to be a sniper using those big guns to score 1shotkills from 2 km away you can but if you weigh yourself down with ammo you will become easily fatigued and your movement will be dropped to movement slower than an overencumbered elder scrolls character that brings us to the map size of the most popular map altis altis is big big big here [40mediatumblrcom] is a toscale illustration of altis compared to other wellknown large maps i used to try to describe battlefield maps to cod players by saying an entire cod map would fit into a bf home base well caspian border fits nicely into the nato air base on altis the little islandlike peninsula on the southern part of altis is just a bit smaller than skyrim yeah altis is big 270 square kilometers of land 16777 square miles and a total playable area that supports gameplay on land air sea and under water of 1000 square kilometers 62137 square miles making altis bigger than fuels map yeah its bigger than fuel nuff said so im getting bored of typing this so ill wrap up with saying this game is awesome if you like huge openworld simulators that openly supports modding speaking of which there is a hao mod thats right you can play halo in arma 3 i know you can play as odsts and unsc marines but im not sure about spartans and covenant as i only just got the game and i havent tried the mods yet i give this game a 810 loosing 2 points due to graphic limitations
