been here since first arma ive seen huge improvements and still a long way to go arma 3 is way better than arma 2 the alpha version itself has fewer bugs than the released version of arma 2  but that doesnt mean it is bug free i play it in a realism unit and we use the game extensively trying to get 100% of what the game can offer either using zeus or other mods to improve the experience the scenario depicts an unstable region currently constituted by two greek islands located to the south of the balkanic peninsula on the aegean sea the first one is stratis agios efstratios  httpswwwgooglecommaps@39512281925013901113z and the second one is altis lemnos  httpswwwgooglecommaps@3990239652522632626328m bohemian crew actually went to those islands and took pictures of the towns located there so the ingame cities looks almost exactly the same as the real cities just like kavala in altis that looks very much the town of limnos httpyoutubee5urndaogpa there are four factions struggling for power in this region they are nato north atlantic treaty organization csat canton protocol strategic alliance treaty aaf altis armed forces and fia freedom and independence army in all missions the game depicts csat as an invading force and nato as the peacekeeping force aaf and fia are local forces and their allignment varies along the missions the game still has some latency issues lagspikes dedicated server crashes frequently the framerate is extremely low tops 25 even using the standard settings over a highend rig the learning curve is very steep if you didnt play the previous titles from the franchise but once you get things going it is some unique fps experience that no other game can give you and ive played enough of them to know about that be aware if youre willing to hop in a server grab your gear walk 10 steps and start killing people this game is not for you this is a complete combat simulation suite focused on realism which means that usually if you spawn too close to action youll die and youll never know where from if you fly your helicopter too close to the objective youll probably be shot down if you drive your hunter directly inside a hostile city youll probably gonna blow from land mines or at soldiers be ready to drive cars or pilot aircraft for 10 minutes then park the vehicles and walk for 5 more minutes prior to hope for any action at all it is a great game and if you are a fan of simulation and combat genres this is the perfect mix of both for some footage check out my youtube channel httpswwwyoutubecomuserpfcvalls
