pros great game with tons of mods and gamemodes the community is huge and there is always going to be players graphics are simply beautiful cons game is unoptimized game may initially be overwhelming to newcomers of the series lack of more indepth audio options may be a turnoff for us 71 surround users or those who just want a greater level of control my review your experience and mileage may vary depending on what you do with arma 3 you can go all vanilla and play campaign or simple multiplayer or you can go with the huge modding community the mods are really what make this game great not in the mood for simple deathmatch play king of the hill with 120 players not in the mood for that try epoch or survival the gameplay is solid and the experience is worth it there is only one con and it may affect you depending on how you like to experience games you are more than likely not going to get 60 fps in this game and probably will be hard to get a solid 30 without the occasional dips this game is highly unoptimized on multiplayer the game runs fine with single player campaign but with multiplayer the netcode is completely weird some mods i can get 60 fps in some i can barely hit 30 regardless if i run on ultra or minimum settings you will only usually have the same fps the server has this was a big problem initially then i just got past it the gameplay more than makes up for it and the experience is more about the community hopefully this will be rectified soon however i highly doubt it especially if you look at dayz audio customization is a problem i have in particular also with all the customization arma 3 allows with the interface they barely have any settings for audio mostly just the general master chat etc i wish i could choose which sounds levels i could adjust i bought this game with the intention of playing epoch since dayz latest update ruined everything i liked about the game and in the end i barely play epoch mostly survival and king of the hill great gametypes and i also highly recommend atlis life in arma 3s current state i would rate it a 710
