where to begin ive been a longtime user and fan of bohemia interactives arma and operation flashpoint series since the original operation flashpoint while i have always enjoyed the series there was always somethingmissing some intangible thing that i couldt quite put my finger on but left my experience not entirely fulfilled because of this i wasnt even going to bother with arma 3 however with steams promotion allowing play for free this weekend i thought id try it out i installed it played the tutorial and played some of the showcase missions and campaign missions what do i think well the devs finally get it they finally finally made the game i always wanted since the first operation flashpoint no more herkyjerky animations no more bad bad dialogue theyve overhauled the graphics engine got what sound like to me professional voice actors and they really turned out a topnotch product this is a serious military sim that is unforgiving and pulls no punches you arent some rapidly healing super soldier you get hit youll probably die even if you patch yourself up with a medkit you are still in pain and that is reflected in the gameplay this is a thinking mans military sim this isnt a call of duty or battlefield game this is to first person shooters as microsofts flight simulator is to flying games its amazing on a rig that can run it the graphics are absolutely amazing the weather effects are top notch and its all on a huge huge map and an insanely detailed one at that so far the campaign is quite entertaining if not a little unforgiving my only quibble with arma 3 is that the ai is a little wacky either you find yourself up against eagle eyed super snipers that can see in the dark or complete morons who will stand stock still and fire at you often the ai is fairly good but man once in a while i havent tried multiplayer yet but i cannot wait to give it a shot i would give this game 4 and a half stars out of 5 a nearly perfect military simulation well done bohemia interactive well done
