recommended
arma 3 is a cross between a game and a military simulator it is more complex than the usual bigname games like call of duty and battlefield making the learning curve potentially intimidating for beginners in reality however if you can handle typical fps games you can figure out the basics of arma 3 in about a week the reward of sticking with it is immersion in massive beautiful outdoor environments the smaller island of the two is about 20 km while the larger one is 270 km tactical play and epic encounters there is something different about scrambling for cover as youre being shot at by an enemy patrol and not knowing where its coming from  and then after you find out having to use compass readings to share that knowledge with your teammates its also incredibly fun to take an ai squad under your command close to an enemy position assigning targets to them individually and then ordering them all to open fire at the same time on the unsuspecting soldiers notwithstanding all of this quite possibly the best part of arma 3 is its open nature while youll probably enjoy playing the stock escape missions youll soon discover that there is a treasure trove of custom scenarios created by the community this is one game that is worth the price just for the community creations alone
